events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell heard the boos directed at him and his teammates as the game slipped away in the fourth quarter.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavaliers booed at home during 'worst' loss this season as Trail Blazers beat Cleveland 103-95

headlines.description: — Terry Rozier had 37 points and 13 assists, and the short-handed Charlotte Hornets beat the Brooklyn Nets 129-128 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rozier has 37 points and 13 assists, Hornets win 129-128 to snap Nets' three-game winning streak

headlines.description: — The last time Miami scored 45 points in a fourth quarter was 1989, long before Pat Riley arrived in South Florida, long before Erik Spoelstra arrived, long before most of the current Heat players were born.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler scores 36, Heat get hot late to top Pacers 142-132 and snap a 3-game slide

events.name: Detroit Pistons at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson scored 42 points, Julius Randle had 29 points and 10 rebounds, and the New York Knicks sent the Detroit Pistons to their franchise-record 16th consecutive loss with a 118-112 victory Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson scores 42, Knicks send Pistons to franchise-record 16th straight loss

headlines.description: — Alex Caruso took the handoff from Nikola Vucevic at the top of the key and dribbled twice to his right before launching a fadeaway 3-pointer over Brook Lopez at the end of...
headlines.shortLinkText: Vucevic and White lead the way as Bulls beat Bucks 120-113 in OT

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 32 points and 11 rebounds, and the Minnesota Timberwolves weathered the absence of leading scorer Anthony Edwards to beat the Utah Jazz 101-90 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Karl-Anthony Towns helps T-wolves beat Jazz 101-90 with Edwards sidelined

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 33 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat LeBron James and the Los Angeles Lakers 133-110 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scores 33 as Thunder beat Lakers 133-110

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Trae Young was practically unstoppable in the fourth quarter, but his defensive stop made the biggest impact against the San Antonio Spurs.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young scores 45 as Hawks rally past Wembanyama, Sochan to hand Spurs 13th straight loss

events.name: LA Clippers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Klay Thompson's fourth-quarter flurry brought back memories of so many other scoring bursts on his impressive list of them.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry, Thompson come up big down the stretch, Warriors hold off Clippers 120-114
